FIFA Leaves Door Open for DPR Korea for 2002 World Cup
SEOUL , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- FIFA major official said on Monday the soccer 's world governing body is still leaving the door open for Democratic People 's Republic of Korea to host a few games of the 2002 World Cup .
Joseph S. Blatter said they are willing to open dialogue with DPR Korea on the issue when he was on a two-day visit after he arrived in Seoul Sunday for the preparations for the games .
Blatter said he had accepted an invitation from DPR Korea to visit the country next fall .
From Seoul , Blatter flies to Tokyo , Japan to see the Toyota Cup , the world club championship .
